title: Bring Out Your Beast
description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

title: Dinner at the Creek
description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

title: Kelsey Quest
description: Kelsey accepts a quest from the Elders of the Creek, but is she ready for her terrifying opponent?

title: Itch to Explore
description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

title: The Future is Cardboard
description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

title: The Curse
description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

title: Ace of Squares
description: Craig vows to make the game of Four Square fun again by challenging its most dominant player!

title: Dog Decider
description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

title: Creek Cart Racers
description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

title: The Brood
description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

title: Escape from Family Dinner
description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

title: The Takeout Mission
description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

title: Doorway to Helen
description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

title: JPony
description: JP decides to follow his heart and tries to join the Horse Girls.

title: The Kid From 3030
description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

title: You're It
description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

title: Bug City
description: Craig discovers a bunch of bugs under a rock and decides to build them a city.

title: The Climb
description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

title: Monster in the Garden
description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

title: Jessica's Trail
description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

title: Too Many Treasures
description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

title: Sunday Clothes
description: JP dirties his last clean clothes and he must wear his Sunday best to the creek.

title: Lost in the Sewer
description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

title: Power Punchers
description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

title: Secret Book Club
description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

title: The Last Kid in the Creek
description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

title: Jextra Perrestrial
description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

title: Under the Overpass
description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

title: The Final Book
description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

title: Vulture's Nest
description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

title: Wildernessa
description: An encounter with Wildernessa, guardian of the wilderness, inspires Kelsey to take up a cause.

title: Big Pinchy
description: JP leads his friends on a voyage to find the biggest crayfish in the creek.

title: The Invitation
description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party…
